To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Arizona Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

All e-mail communications (including complete email chains, email attachments, calendar invitations, and calendar invitation attachments) between a) the members listed below and b) the individuals listed below that c) contain the term "squatting," "squatters," or "transient occupants," and d) were sent or received between 1/1/2023 and the date this request is fulfilled.

a)
Senator Wendy Rogers
Senator David Farnsworth
Senator John Kavanagh
Senator Anthony Kern
Senator Thomas Shope
Senator Justine Wadsack

b) 
Any personnel of the National Rental Home Council with email suffix @rentalhomecouncil.org
Any personnel of Goodman Schwartz Public Affairs with email suffix @goodmanschwartz.com

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Rebecca Burns

title: IACUC reports of concern for animal health and safety

communications.subject: Wisconsin Open Records Act Request: IACUC reports of concern for animal health and safety
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wisconsin Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any records relating to reports and complaints filled by researchers (students and faculty) about concern to animal health and safety across the University of Wisconsin schools including the School of Medicine and Public Health, the School of Veterinary Medicine, College of Agricultural and Life Sciences from January, 1, 2023- present day.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Julieta Cardenas
